{{Infobox language |name=Kera |states=[[Chad]], [[Cameroon]] |speakers=50,000 |date=1993 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Afro-Asiatic |fam2=[[Chadic]] |fam3=[[East Chadic languages|East Chadic]] |fam4=[[East Chadic A languages|East Chadic A]] |fam5=[[Kwang languages|Kwang]] (A.3) |iso3=ker |glotto=kera1255 |glottorefname=Kera }}
'''Kera''' is an [[East Chadic languages|East Chadic language]] spoken by 45,000 people in Southwest [[Chad]] and 6,000 people in North [[Cameroon]].
It was called "Tuburi" by Greenberg, a name shared with [[Tupuri language|Tupuri]].
==Grammar==
Kera is a [[subject–verb–object]] language, using [[preposition]]s. It uses exclusively borderline [[declension|case-marking]].
