{{Infobox language |name=Sinyar |nativename=Shemya |states=[[Chad]] |ethnicity=[[Sinyar people|Sinyar]] |speakers={{sigfig|12300|2}} |date=2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Nilo-Saharan |fam2=[[Central Sudanic languages|Central Sudanic]] |fam3=? (possibly with [[Fongoro language|Fongoro]]) |iso3=sys |glotto=siny1243 |glottorefname=Sinyar }}
'''Shemya''' is the language of the [[Sinyar people]]. It is a [[Central Sudanic language]] spoken in Chad and formerly in [[Darfur]], Sudan. It is variously spelled ''Shamya, Shamyan, Shemya, Sinya,'' and known as ''Symiarta, Taar Shamyan, Zimirra.''
Dimmendaal leaves it as a [[language isolate]]. Blench groups it with [[Formona language|Formona]].
